extends layout

block content
  //- Page header
  section(class='hero is-medium is-info is-bold margin-bottom-4')
    div(class='hero-body has-text-centered')
      div(class='container')
        img(src='/images/logo.png', class='logo')
        h1(class='title') Request Mirror
        h2(class='subtitle') Request Mirror allows you to submit HTTP requests and view the header, query parameters, and body of the request.

  //- Create Mirror button
  div(class='container has-text-centered')
    a(class='button is-info is-outlined is-medium' href='/inspect')
      i(class='fa fa-plus-circle margin-right-1')
      span Create Mirror

  //- Features
  div(class='container')
    h1(class='title has-text-centered margin-top-2') Features
    div(class='columns')

      //- HTTP and HTTPS support
      div(class='column')
        article(class='media')
          figure(class='media-left')
            p(class='image')
              <i class="fa fa-globe fa-4x blue-icon"></i>
          div(class='media-content')
            div(class='content')
              p <strong>HTTP and HTTPS support</strong>
              p Request Mirror has support for both HTTP and HTTPS protocols, meaning that you can test your requests no matter what level of support they have for modern, secure traffic.
              p For security reasons, we do recommend using <strong>HTTPS</strong> whenever possible.

      //- Use any trailing path
      div(class='column')
        article(class='media')
          figure(class='media-left')
            p(class='image')
              <i class="fa fa-location-arrow fa-4x blue-icon"></i>
          div(class='media-content')
            div(class='content')
              p <strong>Use any trailing path</strong>
              p Sometimes, it's not always possible to define the exact URL you use in your application.  Request Mirror allows you to use any URL you like, so long as you used the prescribed prefix.
              p This means that you can use a URL with <string>any</string> valid URL text after the link we provide for logging.

      //- Use any verb
      div(class='column')
        article(class='media')
          figure(class='media-left')
            p(class='image')
              <i class="fa fa-font fa-4x blue-icon"></i>
          div(class='media-content')
            div(class='content')
              p <strong>Use any verb</strong>
              p With Request Mirror, you can specify <span class='pre bold'>GET</span>, <span class='pre bold'>HEAD</span>, <span class='pre bold'>POST</span>, <span class='pre bold'>PUT</span>, <span class='pre bold'>PATCH</span>, <span class='pre bold'>DELETE</span>, <span class='pre bold'>TRACE</span>, or <span class='pre bold'>OPTIONS</span> verb.
              p You can see your request, no matter the type!
